  "prompt": "Can you use a Visa gift card on Amazon?",
  "response": "Yes, you can use a Visa gift card on Amazon. To do so, you need to add the gift card to your Amazon account as a payment method. Here\u2019s how you can do it:\n\n1. Log in to your Amazon account.\n2. Go to \"Your Account\" and then select \"Your Payments.\"\n3. Click on \"Add a payment method.\"\n4. Choose \"Add a credit or debit card.\"\n5. Enter the Visa gift card information (card number, expiration date, and the security code).\n6. Save the card information.\n\nOnce added, you can use the gift card as a payment method for your purchases on Amazon, provided there are enough funds available on the card to cover the transaction. If the balance on the gift card is less than the total purchase amount, you may need to pay the remaining balance with another payment method.",
